This topic describes how to install and configure Twistlock for PCF.
After the install is complete, Twistlock Defender will be running in your environment.

##<a id='install'></a> Import the Twistlock Tile

1. Download the latest Twistlock release from the [Twistlock doc site](https://docs.twistlock.com/docs/latest/download/releases.html).

1. In the Ops Manager Installation Dashboard, click **Import a Product**.

1. Select the tile from the Twistlock release directory.
It can be found in TWISTLOCK-RELEASE/pivotal/twistlock-tile-VERSION.pivotal.


##<a id='install'></a> Retrieve the Install Command

Retrieve the install command from Twistlock Console.
It is used to configure the tile.

1. Log into Twistlock Console.

1. Go to **Manage > Defenders > Deploy**.

1. Choose the DNS name or IP address the PCF Defender will use to connect to Console.
   If a suitable option is not available, go to **Manage > Defenders > Names**, and add a DNS name or IP address to the SAN table.

1. Set the Defender type to **PCF**.

1. Leave the Defender listener type set to **None**.

1. Copy the install command and set it aside.
You will use it in the next section.

    <%= image_tag("install_cmd.png", :width => "600") %>


##<a id='install'></a> Install and Configure Twistlock for PCF

1. Navigate to the Ops Manager Installation Dashboard.

1. Add the Twistlock for PCF tile to your staging area.
Click the **+** button next to the version of the tile you want to install.

    <%= image_tag("add_tile_to_staging.png", :width => "250") %>

1. Click the newly added **Twistlock for PCF** tile.

1. In **Assign AZs and Network Assignments**, specify where Twistlock Defender should run, then click **Save**.

1. In **Twistlock Component Configuration**, enter the install command, then click **Save**.

1. In **Credentials**, enter your Twistlock Console credentials, then click **Save**.
Your [role](https://docs.twistlock.com/docs/latest/access_control/user_roles.html)  must be Defender Manager or higher.

1. Install the Twistlock tile.
Return to the Ops Manager Installation Dashboard, click **Review Pending Changes**, select **Twistlock for PCF**, then click **Apply changes**.

1. After the changes are applied, validate that Twistlock Defender is running.
Log into Twistlock Console, then navigate to **Manage > Defenders > Manage**.
In the table of deployed Defenders, you should see a Defender of type **PCF**.

